<section id="envTactileMessaging" class="section-content section-padding">
    <div>
        <article>
            <h2>Tactile Messaging</h2>
            <div class="content-grid">
                <p>Depth of raised lettering should be greater than or equal to 0.8mm.</p>
                <p>Use sans serif for raised lettering.</p>
                <p><span>Difference between tactile messaging and graphic elements should be 10mm apart.</span></p>
                <div>
                    <!-- @import "img/envTactileMessaging1.kit" -->
                </div>
                <p>Messaging placement should be between 1200mm and 1500mm from the floor.</p>
                <p>Tracking should be no less than 3mm and no greater than four times the stroke width.</p>
                <p>Cap-height should be between 16-50mm.</p>
                <p><span>Mixed case is better than all caps, but use local standards.</span></p>
                <div>
                    <!-- @import "img/envTactileMessaging2.kit" -->
                </div>
                <p>Braille should be placed directly below raised text, but standards vary by region.</p>
                <p>Source: <a href="https://www.rgd.ca/database/files/library/RGD_AccessAbility2_Handbook_2019_06_01(1).pdf">RGD ONTARIO</a></p>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>